        "body": "<p>From <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/56959608/java-jigsaw-modules-what-happened-july-2019?noredirect=1#comment100458099_56959608\">comment<\/a>:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>are there any <strong>examples of simple &quot;hello world&quot; type Jigsaw projects<\/strong> that use third party module dependencies? I can't find any. I tried to create one that depended on slf4j-simple 1.8 (beta) and had trouble.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>From current (Jul. 9, 2019) <a href=\"https://logback.qos.ch/setup.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Logback Setup page<\/a>:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>To use logback-classic in your Maven project, declare the following dependency in your project's pom file.<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n  &lt;groupId&gt;ch.qos.logback&lt;/groupId&gt;\n  &lt;artifactId&gt;logback-classic&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n  &lt;version&gt;1.3.0-alpha4&lt;/version&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p>This added the following files to my project:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>activation-1.1.jar\njavax.mail-1.6.0.jar\nlogback-classic-1.3.0-alpha4.jar\nlogback-core-1.3.0-alpha4.jar\nslf4j-api-1.8.0-beta1.jar\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p><em>module-info.java<\/em><\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>module Test {\n    requires org.slf4j;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p><em>test/Test.java<\/em><\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>package test;\n\nimport org.slf4j.Logger;\nimport org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n\npublic class Test {\n    private static final Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(Test.class);\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        log.info(&quot;Hello World&quot;);\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p><em>Output<\/em><\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-none prettyprint-override\"><code>17:00:20.132 [main] INFO test.Test - Hello World\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Run in jdk-11.0.1 using Eclipse 2018-12.<\/p>\n<p>No trouble encountered with this simple &quot;hello world&quot; type Jigsaw project.<\/p>\n",
